('item-0064',64,'Animals & Classification','A · Hook','Animals & Classification — gate passage','gate','article','','400-460L','Unit-gate UNSEEN passage. How Scientists Group Insects (a NEW topic not read in any lesson: the insect group — 6 legs, 3 body parts, antennae, an exoskeleton instead of a backbone — re-using the vertebrate/invertebrate, trait, main-idea, cause-effect, and diagram-reading skills on fresh content). 415L, informational, ~290 words, includes a labeled diagram of an ant with callouts to its three body parts and six legs. The bin-sort gate item uses a categorize (drag-to-bin) interaction; the drag-to-order gate item is a genuine cause→effect sequence; vocab items are L.3.4 context-clue / prefix-suffix strategy items (e.g. the prefix ''ex-'' in ''exoskeleton'' meaning ''outside,'' context clues for ''antennae''). Must be a topic NOT read in the lessons.'),
