('item-0494',494,'The Human Body','B · Bridge','The Human Body — gate passage','gate','article','','480-540L','Unit-gate UNSEEN passage. The Stomach: Where Food Begins Its Journey — a 520L informational passage explaining, in sequence, how the stomach mashes food into mush and sends it on to help the body. The passage includes a labeled diagram of the digestive path (mouth → throat → stomach → intestine) with arrows showing the order food travels, so visual-integration items have source material. The passage also includes explicit cause-and-effect connections written into the text (for example, ''BECAUSE the stomach squeezes and mixes the food, it turns into a soft mush the body can use,'' and ''The stomach makes juices SO the hard food can break apart''), giving cause/effect items real textual support. This is a digestion topic NOT read in any lesson. Must be a topic NOT read in the lessons.'),
